#* {{quote-book|en|year=1915|chapter=Putting on the Screw|title=Caught in the Net|by={{w|Émile Gaboriau}}|original=Les Esclaves de Paris|location=New York|publisher=Charles Scribner's Sons|pageurl=https://archive.org/details/caughtinnet00gabo/page/22/|page=23|passage=I '''twigged''' him at once, by the description you gave me. I never see a cove togged out as he was,—tall hat, light sit-down-upons, and a short coat—wasn't it cut short! but in really bang-up style.|translation=J'y ai '''reconnu''' le particulier que vous m'avez dit. Bien vêtu, ma foi! Chapeau rogné, tout plat, pantalon clair, en fourreau de parapluie, veston court, oh! mais d'un court... enfin, le dernier genre. }}
#* {{quote-web|en|date=2012-05-30|first=John E.|last=McIntyre| title=A future for copy editors| site=Baltimore Sun| url=http://www.baltimoresun.com/news/language-blog/bal-a-future-for-copy-editors-20120530,0,4576028.story?track=rss| passage=Well, with fewer people doing two or three times the work, you may have already '''twigged''' to this.}}
# To [[understand]] the meaning of (a person); to [[comprehend]].
#: {{ux|en|Do you '''twig''' me?}}
# To [[observe]] [[slyly]]; also, to [[perceive]]; to [[discover]].
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1763|authorlink=Samuel Foote|first=Samuel|last=Foote|title={{w|The Mayor of Garratt}}|others=act 2|passage=Now '''twig''' him; now mind him: mark how he hawls his muscles about.}}
#* {{quote-book|en|year=1863|authorlink=Nathaniel Hawthorne|first=Nathaniel|last=Hawthorne|title=[[gutenberg:8090|Our Old Home]]|passage=This excellent man appears to have sunk into himself in a sitting posture, {{...|with a thin leg crossed over his knee, a book in one hand, and a finger of the other under his chin, I believe, or applied to the side of his nose, or to some equally familiar purpose;}} while his exceedingly homely and wrinkled face, held a little on one side, twinkles at you with the shrewdest complacency, as if he were looking right into your eyes and '''twigged''' something there which you had half a mind to conceal from him.}}

